On May 9, 2022, the President signed into law the "Ukraine Democracy Defense Lend-Lease Act of 2022" (S. 3522). This act grants the authority to lend or lease defense articles to Ukraine and Eastern European countries. The President expressed gratitude to Senate leadership, including Senators Cornyn, Cardin, Wicker, and Shaheen, as well as House leadership, Chairman Meeks, Ranking Member McCaul, and Representatives Joe Wilson, Cohen, Cheney, Malinowski, Waltz, and Slotkin for their leadership in this matter.